        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I am having a problem with acquiring a new connection to an IDS database using pdo_ibm driver.\r\nConnection string: \"ibm: DRIVER={IBM DB2 ODBC DRIVER};DATABASE=zbo; HOSTNAME=IP_ADDR;PORT=9088;PROTOCOL=TCPIP; \"\r\nI get an error:\r\n\r\nSQLSTATE=08001, SQLDriverConnect: -30081 [IBM][CLI Driver] SQL30081N  A communication error has been detected. Communication protocol being used: \"TCP\/IP\".  Communication API being used: \"SOCKETS\".  Location where the error was detected: \"IP_ADDR\".  Communication function detecting the error: \"recv\".  Protocol specific error code(s): \"*\", \"*\", \"0\".  SQLSTATE=0800\r\nwhich I was unable to decipher having the available documentation. \r\nDatabase configuration is also limited due to the fact that it is constantly working in production mode.\r\n\r\nI have managed to come up with a workaround by using this connection string\r\n\"informix: host=IP_ADDR; service=9088; database=zbo; server=db; protocol=onsoctcp; DB_LOCALE=pl_PL.1250; Client_Locale=pl_pl.1250\" \r\nand setting specifically IDS in Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Ibm:_connect()\r\n\r\nI would ask to You, for the future version of Zend, to make Zend\\Db\\Adapter\\Pdo\\Ibm\\Ids.php a seprate Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Abstract with \"informix\" as a _pdoType.\r\n      "
        },
